The paper discusses a framework for implementing asynchronous optimization methods in distributed machine learning, which falls under the category of large-scale machine learning (cs.LG). The framework is designed for distributed computing platforms, which suggests a potential fit for distributed systems (cs.DC) and distributed algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the popularity of asynchronous optimization methods in machine learning, indicating a potential fit for neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper demonstrates the implementation of optimization methods for computer vision tasks, suggesting a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV).
